data.name: plNoFollowWeb.Help
data.value:
If checked, indicates that the destination of user website hyperlinks SHOULD NOT be afforded any additional weight or ranking by user agents which perform link analysis upon web pages (e.g. search engines).
NOTE
This applies to user profile page website links as well as user website links in posts.

data.name: plOverrideTitle.Help
data.value: If checked, the page title set by DotNetNuke will be overriden with the forum name or thread name depending on view (up to 64 chars).

data.name: plNoFollowLatestThreads.Help
data.value:
If checked, indicates that the destination hyperlinks in the initial group view SHOULD NOT be afforded any additional weight or ranking by user agents which perform link analysis upon web pages (e.g. search engines).
NOTE
This applies to the links in initial group view (6,12,24,48, view latest threads) typically seen when first viewing a page with the forum module placed on it.

data.name: plOverrideDescription.Help
data.value: If checked, the page meta description set by DotNetNuke will be overriden with the initial post content at the thread level (when view posts). If in forum view (ie. lists of threads) the description of the forum will be set here (up to 150 chars).

data.name: plSitemapPriority.Help
data.value: This will set the priority level in the sitemap provider (values of 1.0 to .1 work here).

data.name: plOverrideKeyWords.Help
data.value: If checked, the page keywords set by DotNetNuke will be overriden with the forum name and any applied tags (up to 15 total words).
